  "id": "019d2e24-ea47-7493-bb15-f28ebf55d1ac",
  "content": "# HNSW Index Management — Decisions (March 2026)\n\n## Demotion (Warm→Cold)\nLazy orphaning: delete Redb UUID↔HNSW mappings during GC cycle. Single rebuild at end of cycle if any demotions occurred. Not one rebuild per entry.\n\n## Promotion (Cold→Warm)\nSynchronous hnsw_rs insert() — O(log n), sub-millisecond. Recreate Redb mappings. No async needed.\n\n## Rebuild Triggers\n- End of GC cycle (if demotions occurred)\n- After delete_scope\n- After manual corvia_gc_run\n- When orphan ratio > 20%\n- Blue-green pattern: build new index in background, atomic swap under mutex\n\n## Cold Entry Search\nBrute-force cosine scan over Redb-stored embeddings. Only when include_cold=true or Hot+Warm results below relevance threshold. Acceptable up to ~10K cold entries (<10ms).\n\n## PostgresStore\nPartial HNSW indexes with WHERE clause. Tier changes handled automatically by PostgreSQL. No manual rebuild.\n\n## Deferred\nSecondary cold HNSW index — only needed above 50K cold entries.",
